Police in Anambra State have arrested six persons, including a traditional doctor and two women, in connection with the parade of a nude widow. The woman was accused of causing the death of her husband through her alleged infidelity. Commissioner of Police Echeng Echeng, who paraded the suspects at the command’s headquarters in Awka yesterday, said they were identified in a viral video. In the video, the woman was made to sit by her late husband’s body and was later paraded naked on the street of Aguleri in Anambra East Local Government Area.   Residents, scavengers clash as FCTA demolishes illegal…     Akwa Ibom teachers begin indefinite strike     Diri urges politicians to play by the rules   Echeng said investigation revealed that the deceased was ill and actually died at a traditional healing home. “The command’s operatives have arrested six additional suspects, including a native doctor who was identified during the study of the video by police operatives. The native doctor confessed to engaging the deceased in some spiritual cleansing and administering some herbs on him before he died. “It was the native doctor who allegedly told the family of the deceased that his death was caused by his wife’s infidelity. “”The woman has been rescued, taken to hospital and reunited with her family safely. She is in good condition,” Echeng said. The police commissioner also said the command arrested three suspects, who allegedly invaded Ebenebe town in Awka North council of the state a few weeks ago, killing over 20 persons during a funeral.